The course contains basic probability theory and mathematical statistics and includes training for using packages of applied statistics and interpretation of results.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give basic knowledge on probability and statistics and to apply this to simple statistical problems.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course its participant: 1. knows the definition of probability, the multiplication and addition laws of probability, the concept of conditional probability and is able to apply them in solving simpler exercises; 2. knows the basic distributions of random variates; 3. is familiar with basic concepts of statistics; 4. understands the principles of statistical hypothesis testing; 5. is able use statistical software to find the sample characterstics, confidence intervals for the mean, perform the hypothesis testing procedure and interpret the results.
